cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is about deep neural networks and their mechanisms for adjusting complexity. The paper focuses on empirical evidence of two types of units that emerge in overparametrized networks, which are relevant to machine learning and computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for additional research into these mechanisms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
